# -*- encoding: utf-8 -*-
# Arc: WarriorPath | Scene: WarriorQueen7Capital
# Source: C:\Program Files (x86)\Steam\steamapps\common\The Survival of Sarah Rose\game\script.rpy

translate ru strings:

    old "On Sarah's orders, her army had begun to set itself atop the hill that overlooked the Capital."
    new "On Sarah's orders, her army had begun to set itself atop the hill that overlooked the Capital."

    old "The valley beneath and the land between her army and the capital was mostly farmland."
    new "The valley beneath and the land between her army and the capital was mostly farmland."

    old "With the season of winter upon them, the fields were left empty."
    new "With the season of winter upon them, the fields were left empty."

    old "Still, even from so far away, Sarah could see the movements in the Capital."
    new "Still, even from so far away, Sarah could see the movements in the Capital."

    old "The Tribesmen, moving like ants across the walls of the city. The occasional scout group that dared outside."
    new "The Tribesmen, moving like ants across the walls of the city. The occasional scout group that dared outside."

    old "Still, from this position, it was impossible for any Tribesmen to come upon them by surprise."
    new "Still, from this position, it was impossible for any Tribesmen to come upon them by surprise."

    old "The moment even the smallest group left the gates of the Capital, they stood out, black dots against white snow."
    new "The moment even the smallest group left the gates of the Capital, they stood out, black dots against white snow."

    old "As her army prepared, there was a nervous and anxious energy all around."
    new "As her army prepared, there was a nervous and anxious energy all around."

    old "The men were eager for the fight, but equally frightend of it."
    new "The men were eager for the fight, but equally frightend of it."

    old "For most, this carnage did not come natural nor easy."
    new "For most, this carnage did not come natural nor easy."

    old "Turning farmers into soldiers was never easy."
    new "Turning farmers into soldiers was never easy."

    old "And this was what had worried Sarah most."
    new "And this was what had worried Sarah most."

    old "The Tribesmen army, from what she could tell by sight and from her reports, was decidely smaller than her army."
    new "The Tribesmen army, from what she could tell by sight and from her reports, was decidely smaller than her army."

    old "But they were battle-hardend warriors."
    new "But they were battle-hardend warriors."

    old "Every single Tribesmen had been trained from birth to fight."
    new "Every single Tribesmen had been trained from birth to fight."

    old "Most of them were veterans of not just one campaign, but multiple."
    new "Most of them were veterans of not just one campaign, but multiple."

    old "They were eager for the fight, and more than that, they were even eager for a good death."
    new "They were eager for the fight, and more than that, they were even eager for a good death."

    old "For a Tribesmen, to die in combat was such an honorable thing that sometimes after a great battle, some expressed regret for having survived it."
    new "For a Tribesmen, to die in combat was such an honorable thing that sometimes after a great battle, some expressed regret for having survived it."

    old "That was far from how the people of Rosanna lived."
    new "That was far from how the people of Rosanna lived."

    old "Her people yearned for good harvests and easy lives."
    new "Her people yearned for good harvests and easy lives."

    old "But such kindness and soft living as a weakness in times of war."
    new "But such kindness and soft living as a weakness in times of war."

    old "It was a weakness that had exposed them to the occupation of the Tribesmen."
    new "It was a weakness that had exposed them to the occupation of the Tribesmen."

    old "And now, Sarah prayed that her people could be as brutal as they were kind. To be strong today so they might earn easier lives tomorrow."
    new "And now, Sarah prayed that her people could be as brutal as they were kind. To be strong today so they might earn easier lives tomorrow."

    old "From the corner of her eyes, Sarah saw Kate approach."
    new "From the corner of her eyes, Sarah saw Kate approach."

    old "Her voice was soft, filled with a seriousness that was usually lacking."
    new "Her voice was soft, filled with a seriousness that was usually lacking."

    old "Hey. Are your men ready?"
    new "Hey. Are your men ready?"

    old "You know they are."
    new "You know they are."

    old "Of course. Just asking out of habit I guess."
    new "Of course. Just asking out of habit I guess."

    old "The two of them stood for a while in silence."
    new "The two of them stood for a while in silence."

    old "Below the hill, the Capital of Rosanna. Strangely quiet."
    new "Below the hill, the Capital of Rosanna. Strangely quiet."

    old "Does it feel weird? Being home?"
    new "Does it feel weird? Being home?"

    old "I've been home for a while now."
    new "I've been home for a while now."

    old "Yeah...but that's where all your memories took place. Just about everything before you left..."
    new "Yeah...but that's where all your memories took place. Just about everything before you left..."

    old "Left."
    new "Left."

    old "Sarah knew Kate still struggled with what she had done all those years ago."
    new "Sarah knew Kate still struggled with what she had done all those years ago."

    old "The lies. The betrayal."
    new "The lies. The betrayal."

    old "Don't feel bad about it. The lying, I mean."
    new "Don't feel bad about it. The lying, I mean."

    old "She saw Kate look down, the shame was obvious on her face."
    new "She saw Kate look down, the shame was obvious on her face."

    old "I can't help it..."
    new "I can't help it..."

    old "Her voice was soft again, close to a whisper."
    new "Her voice was soft again, close to a whisper."

    old "You were my only friend...and I betrayed even you."
    new "You were my only friend...and I betrayed even you."

    old "What does that say about a person?"
    new "What does that say about a person?"

    old "You did do that. You did plenty of other things."
    new "You did do that. You did plenty of other things."

    old "The thing about you Kate, and you've been like this even when we were kids..."
    new "The thing about you Kate, and you've been like this even when we were kids..."

    old "You let the bad things lay on you, and all the good slips off."
    new "You let the bad things lay on you, and all the good slips off."

    old "You forget every kindness you ever showed me, yet you remember forever the one time you hurt me."
    new "You forget every kindness you ever showed me, yet you remember forever the one time you hurt me."

    old "In her eyes, she saw the glimmer of tears."
    new "In her eyes, she saw the glimmer of tears."

    old "Her own eyes were clear. Unmoving."
    new "Her own eyes were clear. Unmoving."

    old "I'm here today in no small part because of you."
    new "I'm here today in no small part because of you."

    old "Yes, in part of what you did to me all those years ago...but your kindness too."
    new "Yes, in part of what you did to me all those years ago...but your kindness too."

    old "Your betrayal...it doesn't weigh on me. So don't let it weigh on you."
    new "Your betrayal...it doesn't weigh on me. So don't let it weigh on you."

    old "Sarah saw tears fall from Kate's eyes, falling and cutting into the snow."
    new "Sarah saw tears fall from Kate's eyes, falling and cutting into the snow."

    old "Kate never would find the words she wanted to say."
    new "Kate never would find the words she wanted to say."

    old "Come, clear your head."
    new "Come, clear your head."

    old "We have a battle to fight."
    new "We have a battle to fight."

    old "Kate wiped away the tears and nodded."
    new "Kate wiped away the tears and nodded."

    old "Sarah pointed towards the city in the near distance."
    new "Sarah pointed towards the city in the near distance."

    old "That's home. Yeah, for me that's what I think of when I remembered Rosanna all those years."
    new "That's home. Yeah, for me that's what I think of when I remembered Rosanna all those years."

    old "Those halls...my room...the throne...seeing my father and..."
    new "Those halls...my room...the throne...seeing my father and..."

    old "Sarah couldn't say Thomas' name."
    new "Sarah couldn't say Thomas' name."

    old "I lived a whole life in those halls, believing I'd play a role that I never got to play."
    new "I lived a whole life in those halls, believing I'd play a role that I never got to play."

    old "But instead..."
    new "But instead..."

    old "I'm here now."
    new "I'm here now."

    old "And I'm done, crying and worrying over what my life should have been, or could have been."
    new "And I'm done, crying and worrying over what my life should have been, or could have been."

    old "We all only get this one life."
    new "We all only get this one life."

    old "Let neither of us waste it on regret."
    new "Let neither of us waste it on regret."

    old "Sarah and Kate stood together for a moment longer, sharing a silence as only friends could."
    new "Sarah and Kate stood together for a moment longer, sharing a silence as only friends could."

    old "As the army continued its final preparations, Kate left to rejoin her unit."
    new "As the army continued its final preparations, Kate left to rejoin her unit."

    old "Sarah studied the field for a while longer, enjoying the brief solitude."
    new "Sarah studied the field for a while longer, enjoying the brief solitude."

    old "She turned only when she heard the sound of crushing snow."
    new "She turned only when she heard the sound of crushing snow."

    old "Little one."
    new "Little one."

    old "She heard his voice before she saw him."
    new "She heard his voice before she saw him."

    old "Felt her heart at peace."
    new "Felt her heart at peace."

    old "I'm happy you came."
    new "I'm happy you came."

    old "The others are finishing up their preparations. Checking their armor, sharpening their blades."
    new "The others are finishing up their preparations. Checking their armor, sharpening their blades."

    old "My blade is always sharp."
    new "My blade is always sharp."

    old "Of course. I should have known."
    new "Of course. I should have known."

    old "He walked up besides her."
    new "He walked up besides her."

    old "Whenever she saw him, she rememberd how she'd always forget how tall he was."
    new "Whenever she saw him, she rememberd how she'd always forget how tall he was."

    old "Such a towering figure."
    new "Such a towering figure."

    old "Her eyes traced his broad arms that wielded a slab of metal that most would struggle to even lift."
    new "Her eyes traced his broad arms that wielded a slab of metal that most would struggle to even lift."

    old "Will we win today?"
    new "Will we win today?"

    old "He was quiet for a while."
    new "He was quiet for a while."

    old "She asked him becaus she knew he would always give her an honest answer."
    new "She asked him becaus she knew he would always give her an honest answer."

    old "It is possible."
    new "It is possible."

    old "I was hoping for some insight. I could get a peasant boy to tell me that it's possible."
    new "I was hoping for some insight. I could get a peasant boy to tell me that it's possible."

    old "What should I do? Lie and fill your heart with confidence?"
    new "What should I do? Lie and fill your heart with confidence?"

    old "Or lie and make you anxious for the battle to come?"
    new "Or lie and make you anxious for the battle to come?"

    old "I can speak only the truth, Sarah."
    new "I can speak only the truth, Sarah."

    old "And the truth is that victory is not certain. Nor is defeat."
    new "And the truth is that victory is not certain. Nor is defeat."

    old "Yeah, I know."
    new "Yeah, I know."

    old "I guess I just didn't want to hear it."
    new "I guess I just didn't want to hear it."

    old "Remember it."
    new "Remember it."

    old "Your acts shape the world. Your decisions. You will determine this day."
    new "Your acts shape the world. Your decisions. You will determine this day."

    old "Thanks, I didn't have enough on my shoulders."
    new "Thanks, I didn't have enough on my shoulders."

    old "Be grateful."
    new "Be grateful."

    old "Grateful that you are one of the few that can truly act in this world."
    new "Grateful that you are one of the few that can truly act in this world."

    old "Most of the men and women gathered on this field will live or die through no reason, other than the decisions you make."
    new "Most of the men and women gathered on this field will live or die through no reason, other than the decisions you make."

    old "Is it not worse to live like that?"
    new "Is it not worse to live like that?"

    old "Perhaps. But the burden of it..."
    new "Perhaps. But the burden of it..."

    old "The burden is the burden."
    new "The burden is the burden."

    old "I could see it, even in the early days of your training."
    new "I could see it, even in the early days of your training."

    old "You were strong."
    new "You were strong."

    old "He paused, before adding more."
    new "He paused, before adding more."

    old "You are strong now as well."
    new "You are strong now as well."

    old "She realized she still lived by his praise, despite all the years."
    new "She realized she still lived by his praise, despite all the years."

    old "He suddenly went quiet, shifting about in an unusual way."
    new "He suddenly went quiet, shifting about in an unusual way."

    old "Awkwardness from someone unfamiliar to the emotion."
    new "Awkwardness from someone unfamiliar to the emotion."

    old "What? You want to ask me something?"
    new "What? You want to ask me something?"

    old "As per usual, he coverd his vulnerabilities with pretend anger."
    new "As per usual, he coverd his vulnerabilities with pretend anger."

    old "It's nothing!"
    new "It's nothing!"

    old "He shouted."
    new "He shouted."

    old "For all the world, that mask worked."
    new "For all the world, that mask worked."

    old "But he was a fool for trying it on the only person that saw through it."
    new "But he was a fool for trying it on the only person that saw through it."

    old "Come on, ask me. I can see something is on your mind."
    new "Come on, ask me. I can see something is on your mind."

    old "And shouting at me doesn't scare me. It hasn't scared me for a while."
    new "And shouting at me doesn't scare me. It hasn't scared me for a while."

    old "I wanted to ask you to meet with me."
    new "I wanted to ask you to meet with me."

    old "Meet?"
    new "Meet?"

    old "If we win this battle today...if we survive..."
    new "If we win this battle today...if we survive..."

    old "I know that you will have many things to do...politics, coronations, and other such absurdities."
    new "I know that you will have many things to do...politics, coronations, and other such absurdities."

    old "But I...I wanted to ask if you would meet with me."
    new "But I...I wanted to ask if you would meet with me."

    old "Atilla pointed into the far distance, a slight way off from the city."
    new "Atilla pointed into the far distance, a slight way off from the city."

    old "The royal forests that lay to the north of the capital. Her family had used it for hunting."
    new "The royal forests that lay to the north of the capital. Her family had used it for hunting."

    old "We can meet there..."
    new "We can meet there..."

    old "You know, if you just want to..."
    new "You know, if you just want to..."

    old "Sarah didn't finish her sentence."
    new "Sarah didn't finish her sentence."

    old "There are rooms in the castle, private rooms where we can-"
    new "There are rooms in the castle, private rooms where we can-"

    old "His face was still flustered."
    new "His face was still flustered."

    old "No...it's not that, it's...please meet me in the forest...after."
    new "No...it's not that, it's...please meet me in the forest...after."

    old "Sure, but only because you're acting sort of..."
    new "Sure, but only because you're acting sort of..."

    old "You know, I've called you a lot of things in my life."
    new "You know, I've called you a lot of things in my life."

    old "But until now, I never thought I'd call you cute."
    new "But until now, I never thought I'd call you cute."

    old "She saw a panic on his face."
    new "She saw a panic on his face."

    old "Watch your tongue!"
    new "Watch your tongue!"

    old "Sarah smiled, sticking out her tongue at him."
    new "Sarah smiled, sticking out her tongue at him."

    old "The two of them laughed. A moment where it all felt normal."
    new "The two of them laughed. A moment where it all felt normal."

    old "Before the carnage."
    new "Before the carnage."

    old "Hours later, Sarah rode out at the front of her army."
    new "Hours later, Sarah rode out at the front of her army."

    old "A last inspection, though it didn't matter. She knew they were ready."
    new "A last inspection, though it didn't matter. She knew they were ready."

    old "All of them stood at attention."
    new "All of them stood at attention."

    old "United. Disciplined. Ready."
    new "United. Disciplined. Ready."

    old "Even the Rosannan peasants seemed like daunting soldiers with their armor."
    new "Even the Rosannan peasants seemed like daunting soldiers with their armor."

    old "As she rode along the front of the line, soldiers greeted her."
    new "As she rode along the front of the line, soldiers greeted her."

    old "The Legions of Mythran, send by Gilead, greeted her with raised fists."
    new "The Legions of Mythran, send by Gilead, greeted her with raised fists."

    old "So trained and uniform, they almost didn't seem like individual soldiers."
    new "So trained and uniform, they almost didn't seem like individual soldiers."

    old "In the rear, she saw the siege weapons she had brought, aimed at the city."
    new "In the rear, she saw the siege weapons she had brought, aimed at the city."

    old "Sarah looked at her army."
    new "Sarah looked at her army."

    old "There were her own soldiers from the mercenary company."
    new "There were her own soldiers from the mercenary company."

    old "Then there were her own people."
    new "Then there were her own people."

    old "She could see her army still carried the losses of their previous encounter with the Tribesmen."
    new "She could see her army still carried the losses of their previous encounter with the Tribesmen."

    old "They were not at full strength."
    new "They were not at full strength."

    old "In the valley below, she saw the Tribesmen armies gather."
    new "In the valley below, she saw the Tribesmen armies gather."

    old "Their position on the hill was an advantage. It allowed them to fire on the Capital while staying out of range from the Tribesmen and their archers."
    new "Their position on the hill was an advantage. It allowed them to fire on the Capital while staying out of range from the Tribesmen and their archers."

    old "Being uphill also meant that the Tribesmen cavalry would not be able to carry out a charge as easily."
    new "Being uphill also meant that the Tribesmen cavalry would not be able to carry out a charge as easily."

    old "Still, she knew the Tribesmen were equally skilled at war."
    new "Still, she knew the Tribesmen were equally skilled at war."

    old "Below they had gathered outside of the city, lined up in their own formations."
    new "Below they had gathered outside of the city, lined up in their own formations."

    old "They were not going to wait out their fate inside of the city walls. They had come to meet them on the battlefield."
    new "They were not going to wait out their fate inside of the city walls. They had come to meet them on the battlefield."

    old "For now, each army waited, anxious and restless."
    new "For now, each army waited, anxious and restless."

    old "Sarah had relied on Lady Carolyn's spy network in the Capital to stay informed."
    new "Sarah had relied on Lady Carolyn's spy network in the Capital to stay informed."

    old "Ever since the Tribesmen had occupied the city, it had been reduced to a husk of its former glory."
    new "Ever since the Tribesmen had occupied the city, it had been reduced to a husk of its former glory."

    old "Most of the noble families had fled during The Fall, taking with them whatever they could carry."
    new "Most of the noble families had fled during The Fall, taking with them whatever they could carry."

    old "Those families that didn't flee, or failed to, quickly learned that the Tribesmen culture had no understanding of nobility or titles."
    new "Those families that didn't flee, or failed to, quickly learned that the Tribesmen culture had no understanding of nobility or titles."

    old "Being an old family meant nothing to the Tribesmen."
    new "Being an old family meant nothing to the Tribesmen."

    old "Their estates were taken over, their fortunes looted."
    new "Their estates were taken over, their fortunes looted."

    old "There was hardly any economy to speak of. Instead, the Tribesmen simply looted and carried off their wealth back to their capital of Al'Gahaem."
    new "There was hardly any economy to speak of. Instead, the Tribesmen simply looted and carried off their wealth back to their capital of Al'Gahaem."

    old "And so, the cities of Rosanna dwindled and died."
    new "And so, the cities of Rosanna dwindled and died."

    old "Extracting more wealth was the only objective."
    new "Extracting more wealth was the only objective."

    old "And after the easiest things were stolen, they went after the harder things."
    new "And after the easiest things were stolen, they went after the harder things."

    old "Rounding up citizens, driving them into the mines and forcing them to work endlessly to produce more."
    new "Rounding up citizens, driving them into the mines and forcing them to work endlessly to produce more."

    old "More iron. More coal. More gold."
    new "More iron. More coal. More gold."

    old "They were made to work until their hands broke, and then others would take their place."
    new "They were made to work until their hands broke, and then others would take their place."

    old "But the Tribesmen were not rulers. They had no care for even the things they exploited."
    new "But the Tribesmen were not rulers. They had no care for even the things they exploited."

    old "So over the years, the mines collapsed, until even those offered up no more."
    new "So over the years, the mines collapsed, until even those offered up no more."

    old "And in the end, when nearly everything had been stolen, the people learned that there was still more to be taken from them."
    new "And in the end, when nearly everything had been stolen, the people learned that there was still more to be taken from them."

    old "Today, the Tribesmen made most of their wealth off the slave trade."
    new "Today, the Tribesmen made most of their wealth off the slave trade."

    old "Raiding the villages, town and cities."
    new "Raiding the villages, town and cities."

    old "Whenever some local warlord needed money, they would send more slaves into the desert."
    new "Whenever some local warlord needed money, they would send more slaves into the desert."

    old "So, year on year, the lands of Rosanna dwindled in resources and people, leaving it desolate and cold."
    new "So, year on year, the lands of Rosanna dwindled in resources and people, leaving it desolate and cold."

    old "Sarah felt her heart tremble at the sight of the destruction."
    new "Sarah felt her heart tremble at the sight of the destruction."

    old "But it would end today."
    new "But it would end today."

    old "One way or another."
    new "One way or another."

    old "Sarah drew her blade from its sheath and held it up in the air."
    new "Sarah drew her blade from its sheath and held it up in the air."

    old "The steel from the blade, glimmered."
    new "The steel from the blade, glimmered."

    old "She cried out her command, and one by one, Sarah heard the loud thuds of the trebuchet slings."
    new "She cried out her command, and one by one, Sarah heard the loud thuds of the trebuchet slings."

    old "She watched as the giant boulders soared through the air."
    new "She watched as the giant boulders soared through the air."

    old "Before they could even land, Sarah saw the Tribesmen react."
    new "Before they could even land, Sarah saw the Tribesmen react."

    old "Their clustered army broke, all at once, like an ant colony seperating into countless units."
    new "Their clustered army broke, all at once, like an ant colony seperating into countless units."

    old "All together, they surged forward to the sound of a Tribal warhorn."
    new "All together, they surged forward to the sound of a Tribal warhorn."

    old "When the rocks from the trebuchets finally landed, they struck only a handful of Tribesmen."
    new "When the rocks from the trebuchets finally landed, they struck only a handful of Tribesmen."

    old "Behind their army, some of the boulders struck against the walls and landed inside of the city, sending up smoke."
    new "Behind their army, some of the boulders struck against the walls and landed inside of the city, sending up smoke."

    old "Carried on the wind, Sarah heard the nearing battle cries of the Tribesmen as they surged across the snowy field."
    new "Carried on the wind, Sarah heard the nearing battle cries of the Tribesmen as they surged across the snowy field."

    old "Their horses were powerful, Desert trained."
    new "Their horses were powerful, Desert trained."

    old "Even despite the snow, they moved fast and decisive."
    new "Even despite the snow, they moved fast and decisive."

    old "They would clear the distance between their armies in no time at all."
    new "They would clear the distance between their armies in no time at all."

    old "She doubted her siege weapons would even be able to reload in time for a second salvo."
    new "She doubted her siege weapons would even be able to reload in time for a second salvo."

    old "Sarah cried out her second command, and her army began to move as one."
    new "Sarah cried out her second command, and her army began to move as one."

    old "Moving forward, they took to the field, guarding all the approaches on the hill, moving towards the Tribesmen."
    new "Moving forward, they took to the field, guarding all the approaches on the hill, moving towards the Tribesmen."

    old "Sarah heard the war drum beat, mixing with the war cries of the approaching Tribesmen."
    new "Sarah heard the war drum beat, mixing with the war cries of the approaching Tribesmen."

    old "She herself fell back into the center of her army, able to overlook and issue commands in every direction."
    new "She herself fell back into the center of her army, able to overlook and issue commands in every direction."

    old "The distance between her army and the Tribesmen had shrunk."
    new "The distance between her army and the Tribesmen had shrunk."

    old "Now so close, she could hear the beating and stomping of their horses."
    new "Now so close, she could hear the beating and stomping of their horses."

    old "Snow dusted up as the horde closed the gap."
    new "Snow dusted up as the horde closed the gap."

    old "Then, rushing up all as one, their armies connected."
    new "Then, rushing up all as one, their armies connected."

    old "A violent exploison of steel, horses and men, clashing into each other."
    new "A violent exploison of steel, horses and men, clashing into each other."

    old "Instantly, the Tribesmen cut deep into their front lines."
    new "Instantly, the Tribesmen cut deep into their front lines."

    old "The surging power of their cavalry charge was muted by moving uphill, but still it was stunning to see."
    new "The surging power of their cavalry charge was muted by moving uphill, but still it was stunning to see."

    old "Sarah watched with awe as the first lines broke and the Tribesmen cut through."
    new "Sarah watched with awe as the first lines broke and the Tribesmen cut through."

    old "They swung their curved blades with skill, finding the gaps in between the formation to strike at individual soldiers."
    new "They swung their curved blades with skill, finding the gaps in between the formation to strike at individual soldiers."

    old "Sarah watched as countless men died."
    new "Sarah watched as countless men died."

    old "But even as the screams rose, she saw that it was not so one-sided."
    new "But even as the screams rose, she saw that it was not so one-sided."

    old "With their momentum broken on the first lines, the Tribesmen now fought on equal footing with her own soldiers."
    new "With their momentum broken on the first lines, the Tribesmen now fought on equal footing with her own soldiers."

    old "Spearmen raised up their weapons, stabbing them madly towards the Tribesmen."
    new "Spearmen raised up their weapons, stabbing them madly towards the Tribesmen."

    old "When their weapons found no purchase in the Tribesmen, they would cut into their horses."
    new "When their weapons found no purchase in the Tribesmen, they would cut into their horses."

    old "Stumbling, she saw one of the great beasts falling, dragging along its rider."
    new "Stumbling, she saw one of the great beasts falling, dragging along its rider."

    old "Once too the ground, they made easy killing."
    new "Once too the ground, they made easy killing."

    old "Some of the Tribesmen, nearest to the front, leapt from their horses with almost impossible acrobatics."
